HEADWORD: Scentful
<hw>Scent"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
scent or odor; odorous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>scentful</xex>
nosegay.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of quick or keen smell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>scentful</qex> osprey by the rock had fished.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scentingly</ent>⟦br⟧
